    <p>KUALA LUMPUR • Bad­minton World Fed­er­a­tion pres­i­dent and 1996 Olympic gold medal­list Poul-Erik Hoyer has re­vealed that he has Parkin­son’s dis­ease, but will stay on in his role.</p>
    <p>The for­mer world No. 1 and Dan­ish bad­minton great, 54, was di­ag­nosed with the de­gen­er­a­tive con­di­tion “some years ago”, a state­ment said on Thurs­day.</p>


